; Multiple properties: 3 bad properties, mix of SAT and UNSAT
; Tests multi-property handling
; Expected: SAT (first bad is reachable: x == x is always true)
1 sort bitvec 8
2 sort bitvec 1
3 input 1 x
4 input 1 y
; bad[0]: x == x (trivially SAT)
5 eq 2 3 3
6 bad 5
; bad[1]: x + y == x - y AND y != 0 (UNSAT: requires 2y==0 but y!=0, only when y=128)
; Actually 2*128=0 mod 256, so y=128 works: SAT
7 add 1 3 4
8 sub 1 3 4
9 eq 2 7 8
10 zero 1
11 neq 2 4 10
12 and 2 9 11
13 bad 12
